ParameterInfo.description: Input data to convert the SVG to PDF file.

Operation.description: This is generic Scalable Vector Graphics (SVG) conversion operation that converts the given SVG file into PDF file. SVG is an XML-based markup language for describing two dimensional based vector graphics. SVG is used to define graphics for the Web This operation takes SVG file as input and generates the output file in PDF format.
Operation.name: convertSVG
Operation.returnDescription:
The FMS file ticket of the generated file

The following errors may be returned:

375003     The file ticket is invalid.
375004     "%1$" is not supported for an output type
Operation.useCase: 1)Traceability matrix is rendered using SVG format in ActiveWorkspace secondary work area. After generating traceability matrix,  user clicks on  “Print traceability matrix” command to download to PDF file and print it.

ParameterInfo.description: Input for the operation to create/insert requirements(s) and/or update the contents of existing requirement occurrences.

Operation.description: This operation creates child occurrences of SpecElement type and its subtypes to a selected parent RequirementSpec or inserts new SpecElement occurrence(s) after a specified selected sibling occurrence or updates the contents of existing requirement occurrence(s). Creation, insertion or updation requires the parent RequirementSpec to be viewed and edited in CKEditor, which is visible when the parent occurrence is opened in documentation tab of ACE panel in edit mode. Updated or newly created requirement occurrences are saved in HTML format and are rendered in HTML viewer in the documentation tab.
Operation.name: createOrUpdateContents
Operation.returnDescription:
If successful, ServiceData containing newly created objects is returned.
If an error occurs then ServiceData will contain partial error.
The following partial errors may be returned:
141023: The object has been modified. Please refresh the object before editing.
159008: The object can not be added as it is not a supported type.
Operation.useCase:
Use Case 1: Create a new Requirement occurrence as a child of an empty Requirement Specification parent
User loads the requirement specification in ACE (Active Content Experience) panel and then navigates to documentation tab. User clicks on "Start Edit" option present in the toolbar. This loads CKEditor (HTML editor) inside the documentation tab. The Requirement Specification name is rendered as a title in documentation tab. On clicking the "new requirement" button icon of the CKEditor toolbar, a widget appears in the text area, with regions for content, title and a requirement icon. Inside the "Title" content control, user types-in the name of new SpecElement occurrence. Clicking on "Content" with right mouse button, requirement types appear. User selects any of the available types by clicking on the type. Beneath the Content type, user writes in the content inside a content controller, which is the Body Text of the new requirement. After adding this new requirement, clicking on "Save" button in AWC toolbar, the new requirement is saved in HTML format.

Use Case 2: Insert new requirement(s) after a specific requirement occurrence
User loads the requirement specification in ACE (Active Content Experience) panel and then navigates to documentation tab. User clicks on "Start Edit" option present in the toolbar. This loads CKEditor (HTML editor) inside the documentation tab. The Requirement Specification name is rendered as a title alongwith the children requirement inside the edit area of CKEditor. User selects the content of one of the intermediate requirements inside the editor. User then clicks on "new requirement" button icon of the CKEditor toolbar. A widget appears in the text area, with regions for content, title and icon beneath the previously selected requirement content. User adds multiple such requirements in this way. After inserting the new requirement(s), user clicks on "Save" button in AWC toolbar, resulting into saving of the new requirement(s) in HTML format.

Use Case 3: Update content of existing requirement(s)
User loads the requirement specification in ACE (Active Content Experience) panel and then navigates to documentation tab. User clicks on "Start Edit" option present in the toolbar. This loads CKEditor (HTML editor) inside the documentation tab. The Requirement Specification name is rendered as a title alongwith the children requirement inside the edit area of CKEditor. User selects the content of one of the intermediate requirements inside the editor. User then edits the content by adding/deleting text in content controller. User can add multiple such requirements in this way. After updating the content(s) the requirement(s), user clicks on "Save" button in AWC toolbar, resulting into updating of the body text for this requirement(s) in HTML format.

Use Case 4: Insert new requirement occurrence(s) and edit contents of existing occurrence(s)
User performs operations mentioned in use case #2 and use case #3 in a single edit session followed by a subsequent save. All the newly added requirement occurrences(s) are saved and the edited contents of existing requirement(s) are updated in HTML format.

ParameterInfo.description: Input for the operation to create or update the contents of derived Requirement objects.

Operation.description: This operation retrieves the contents of the FullText dataset for input Requirement Revision objects and sets the same contents on the derived Requirement Revision objects. As part of this operation, all the text and images are copied to the derived Requirement Revision objects. This operation is done in background for performance reasons.
Operation.name: setContentsAsync
Operation.returnDescription: This is an asynchronous method, there is no return value.
Operation.useCase:
Set FullText dataset contents on derived Requirement:
User loads the requirement specification which has been derived previously in ACE (Active Content Experience) panel. User selects a Requirement and clicks on documentation tab and edits the contents of Requirement in CKEditor and clicks on save. The contents of master Requirement are saved. The contents of derived Requirement are saved in the background as part of this operation. User opens the derived Requirement and views the updated contents. If the derived Requirement is also loaded when master Requirement is loaded in ACE, then user has to refresh the documentation tab to see the updated contents.

ParameterInfo.description: The data required to retrieve Requirement specification information of the selected Requirement Specification in Teamcenter.

Operation.description: This operation exports the objects participating in the selected Requirement Specification, their properties, and the linked objects in a JSON file or REQIF file. Linked objects are the objects that have FND_TraceLink relation in Teamcenter. This exported information from the JSON file is useful for generating a preview when user chooses to "import as child". Requirement specifications in REQIF format (Requirements Interchange format) can be imported back in other requirement management tools.
Operation.name: exportSpecifications
Operation.returnDescription:
The specification elements, relations and their property information with structure hierarchy.

The following partial errors may be returned:
375001 - An internal error has occurred in the Requirements Management module.
375005 - The selected input object is not an business object of type Awb0Element.
375006 - The given mode is either empty or is invalid.
Operation.useCase:
• User loads the requirement specification in ACE (Active Content Experience) panel. The ACE panel is used for smart navigation of occurrences in a structure. User selects the command to export the specification to ReqIf format. This will populate all the property metadata information in the export panel so that user can do the type and property mapping. User clicks on the export button to export the specification to ReqIF format.
    • User loads the requirement specification in ACE (Active Content Experience) panel and selects the command to import specification. This will load the import panel. User browses the word document to import and selects “import as child”.

ParameterInfo.description: The data required to retrieve Requirement specification information of the selected Requirement Specification in Teamcenter.

Operation.description: This is an asynchronous operation that exports the objects participating in the selected Requirement Specification, their properties, and the linked objects in a REQIF file. Linked objects are the objects that have FND_TraceLink relation in Teamcenter. Requirement specifications in REQIF format (Requirements Interchange format) can be imported back in other requirement management tools.
Operation.name: exportSpecificationsAsync
Operation.returnDescription: This is an asynchronous method, there is no return value.
Operation.useCase: • User loads the Requirement Specification in ACE (Active Content Experience) panel and selects the command to export the specification to REQIF format. User will select Type and the properties to be exported in the REQIF file. User chooses to execute the operation in background and clicks on the export button. User will be notified once the export is successful.

ParameterInfo.description: The data required to retrieve type and property information of the selected Requirement Specification in Teamcenter.

Operation.description: This operation retrieves the metadata of types of objects participating in the Requirement specification and the metadata of its properties. It also returns the metadata of the linked objects. Linked objects are the objects that have FND_TraceLink relation in Teamcenter. This metadata information is useful for the client to decide the types and properties to be used for import or export purpose.
Operation.name: getSpecificationMetadata
Operation.returnDescription:
The response structure is a container to hold the types and property related information.
The following partial errors may be returned
375001 - An internal error has occurred in the Requirements Management module.
159005 - The selected input object is not an business object of type Awb0Element.
375006 - The input type of object is invalid.
375007 - The input property is invalid.
Operation.useCase:
User loads the requirement specification in ACE (Active Content Experience) panel. The ACE panel is used for smart navigation of occurrences in a structure.
User selects the command to export the specification to ReqIf format. This will populate all the property metadata information in the export panel so that user can do the type and property mapping. User clicks on the export button to export the specification to ReqIF format.

User logs into Active Workspace and clicks on the import to ReqIF command and chooses a ReqIF file for import. This will populate all the property metadata information in the import panel so that user can do the type and property mapping. User clicks on the import button to import the ReqIF file and create a specification in Teamcenter.

ParameterInfo.description: The product and the configuration rules to use to configure the product and get back a page of occurrences. A GetSpecificationInput object can be passed in as input in order to get the contents of occurrences.

Operation.description: This operation retrieves a page of occurrences in a product and returns the contents of a page of occurrences in the form of a HTML buffer which can be rendered in a HTML viewer. The input and output also contains a cursor that defines the place to start the next page location so that the contents of next page of occurrences can be retrieved.
Operation.name: getSpecificationSegment
Operation.returnDescription:
The contents of a page of configured occurrences in the product configured by the specified configuration rules in the input. The response structure contains the string buffer of the HTML buffer that has the stitched contents of a page of occurrences. The following partial errors may be returned:
159001: An internal error has occurred in the Requirements Management module.
159002 : The selected input object is not an BusinessObject of type Awb0Element.
126002 : No Adapter could be found to handle the Product. The system has not been adequately enhanced or customised to deal with the data given to it as input.

ParameterInfo.description: Structure represents the parameters required as input to display traceability matrix between the source and target structures.

Operation.description: This operation retrieves all the data required to display the traceability matrix between the source and target structures. The tracelinks between ItemRevision to ItemRevision, ItemRevision to occurrence and occurrence to occurrence are shown in the traceability matrix. It can retrieve tracelinks for either one level or can traverse through all the children. This operation will also get information about defining and complying objects of the tracelinks.
Operation.name: getTraceabilityMatrix
Operation.returnDescription:
Returns all the information required to be displayed on the traceability matrix. It contains the objects to be displayed as rows and columns, number of tracelinks on the child objects and information of the tracelinks between the displayed row and column objects. This structure will also have all the required information of the linked objects such as object name, object type, id and clear text property.

159001-An internal error has occurred in the Requirements Management module.
159002-The selected input object is not a business object of type Awb0Element.
126002-No Adapter could be found to handle the Product. The system has not been adequately enhanced or customized to deal with the data given to it as input.
Operation.useCase:
1) User clicks on the “traceability matrix” button to view the traceability matrix within the structure. Direct tracelinks between the children of the selected structure will be displayed.
2) User clicks on the “traceability matrix” button to view the traceability matrix between two different structures.
3) User can either choose to view only the direct tracelinks or can view tracelinks for all the child objects of the selected structures.

ParameterInfo.description: Input for the operation to get the traceability matrix.

Operation.description: This operation retrieves all the data required to display the traceability matrix between the source and target structures. The tracelinks between ItemRevision to ItemRevision, ItemRevision to occurrence and occurrence to occurrence are shown in the traceability matrix. It can retrieve tracelinks for either one level or can traverse through all the children. This operation will also get information about defining and complying objects of the tracelinks. Run in background will always be true for this operation.
Operation.name: getTraceabilityMatrixAsync
Operation.returnDescription: This is an asynchronous method, there is no return value.

ParameterInfo.description: The Input to move the occurrences within the specification.

Operation.description:
This operation moves the occurrences in the specification using “newParaNumber”.
This operation rearranges one or many objects within a specification.
For example - If a Requirement has Paragraph Number as “1.1” and user edits to “3.2”, then the Requirement will be moved to the new position “3.2” in the Specification.
If user does not provide “newParaNumber” then it uses input operation argument as below.
Following are currently supported values for input operation argument.
1-Move up - Moves the selected occurrence up within the same parent hierarchy.
2-Move down- Moves the selected occurrence down within the same parent hierarchy.
3-Promote- Moves the selected occurrence to its grand parent within the same specification.
4-Demote- Moves the selected occurrence as a child of the immediate sibling above the selected occurrence.
Operation.name: moveOccurrences
Operation.returnDescription:
The updated occurrence after the movement of occurrence within the specification.
The following partial errors may be returned :
126002-No Adapter could be found to handle the product.
126204-The creation of a BOM Line from cached information has failed.
266001-The Move up action failed because the selected Requirement does not have a sibling above its current position. 266002-The Move down action failed because the selected Requirement does not have a sibling below its current position.
266003-The promote action failed because the selected Requirement does not have a grandparent.
266004-The demote action failed because the selected Requirement does not have a sibling above its current position. 266005-Edit Paragraph Number failed because the number entered is invalid.
266022-Edit Paragraph Number failed because input object is invalid.
Operation.useCase:
User loads the specification in ACE (Active Content Experience) panel. User Clicks on reorder button. The Paragraph Number column become editable. User updates new number for one or many occurrences in the Contents panel and clicks on save button. This actions will rearranges the occurrence with in the specification.

User loads a structure in ACE (Active Content Experience) panel. The ACE panel is used for smart navigation of occurrences in a structure.
User selects an occurrence in the structure and clicks on the MoveUp button in the command bar. This action will move the selected occurrence up within the same parent hierarchy

User loads a structure in ACE (Active Content Experience) panel. The ACE panel is used for smart navigation of occurrences in a structure.
User selects an occurrence in the structure and clicks on the MoveDown button in the command bar. This action will move the selected occurrence down within the same parent hierarchy.

User loads a structure in ACE (Active Content Experience) panel. The ACE panel is used for smart navigation of occurrences in a structure.
User selects an occurrence in the structure and clicks on the Promote button in the command bar. This action will move the selected occurrence to its grand parent within the structure.

User loads a structure in ACE (Active Content Experience) panel. The ACE panel is used for smart navigation of occurrences in a structure.
User selects an occurrence in the structure and clicks on the Demote button in the command bar. This action will move the selected occurrence as a child of the immediate sibling above the selected occurrence.

ParameterInfo.description: Input to save and refresh the traceability matrix.

Operation.description:
Traceability matrix shows the tracelinks between source and target structure in matrix format.
This operation saves or refreshes the generated traceability matrix as a Teamcenter object in target depending on the action done by user. If user opens saved matrix then on saves again, this operation will fetch all the newly created tracelinks from database and updates the same object.
Operation.name: saveTraceabilityMatrix
Operation.returnDescription:
If successful, ServiceData containing updated objects is returned.
If an error occurs then ServiceData will contain partial error.
The following partial errors may be returned:
375001:An internal error has occurred in the Requirements Management module.
375002:The traceability matrix object could not be saved because it is invalid.
375003:The source or the target object in the matrix input is invalid.
375004:The target folder is locked.
Operation.useCase:
1)Once user generates the traceability matrix for required structure(s), then user will be able to save the matrix for offline view using “Save Tracebility Matrix” command.
2)User can open offline saved matrix and do the modification and save it again. In this case it will fetch the all newly created tracelinks form database and update the same object.

StructElement.description: The product context associated with the occurrence.
StructElement.name: contextInfo

StructElement.description: List of parent occurrences for which children are desired.
StructElement.name: parentOccurrences

StructElement.description: The context information including filter, configuration, attached data criteria and page size. The page size controls the number of child occurrences to be returned.
StructElement.name: inputCtxt

StructElement.description: If true, only the next level child occurrences are returned. Otherwise child occurrences from multiple level are returned depending on page size as given in input context.
StructElement.name: firstLevelOnly

StructElement.description: The starting occurrence tag from which we want to get the contents of a Page of Occurrences.
StructElement.name: startOcc

StructElement.description: The ending occurrence tag upto which we want to get the contents of a Page of Occurrences.
StructElement.name: endOcc

StructElement.description: Positive integer mentioning the the number of occurrences to be returned.
StructElement.name: pageSize

Struct.description: The cusor has the information about loading the next set of child occurrences for given parents. It also has Awb0ProductContextInfo and input context which captures the product and configuration information.
Struct.name: ChildOccNextCursor

StructElement.description: The type of operation to perform. Currently this is unused and the value will be empty.
StructElement.name: operationType

StructElement.description: A list of input objects of type Requirement Revision to query the contents of FullText dataset and copy the contents to derived FullText.
StructElement.name: objects

Struct.description: Represents the input data containing a list of input objects whose contents are to be copied to the derived Requirement contents.
Struct.name: ContentInput

StructElement.description: The list of parent occurrences, Awb0ProductContextInfo, page size, page indexes ( start,end).
StructElement.name: cursor

StructElement.description: If true, the next page of occurrences returned else the previous page of occurrences will be returned.
StructElement.name: goForward

Struct.description: The information required to get the next or previous set of child occurrences of an given parent occurrence.
Struct.name: GetNextChildOccData

StructElement.description: It contains the HTML buffer retrieved for the occurrences and the cursor data.
StructElement.name: output

StructElement.description: The Service data.
StructElement.name: serviceData

Struct.description: The HTML contents of resulting occurrences found in the configured product, filtered and sorted by the criteria requested in the input to the service. This data structure also returns a cursor which can be sent back to the same SOA service operation call to in order to rerieve more pages of results.
Struct.name: GetSpecResponse

StructElement.description: Array of Awb0Element for which HTML contents are to be retrieved.
StructElement.name: inputObjects

StructElement.description: Specifies the input information including configuration rules, page size of number of occurrences to fetch, filtering and sorting criteria as well as criteria to fetch atachments.
StructElement.name: inputCtxt

StructElement.description: The information required to get the next or previous set of child occurrences of an given parent occurrence.
StructElement.name: nextOccData

StructElement.description: Options used to process data
StructElement.name: options

StructElement.description: Unique ID token.This is optional parameter.
StructElement.name: clientId

Struct.description: The information required to get the contents of child occurrences, input context, flag to indicate one level or all levels and a flag to indicate if specification is in edit mode.
Struct.name: GetSpecSegmentInput

StructElement.description: A list of configuration rules to apply to the product before returning the resulting occurrences.
StructElement.name: configuration

StructElement.description: The number of occurrences to be  returned in response of this operation. This determines the occurrence page size.
StructElement.name: pageSize

StructElement.description: The StructureContext object containing configuration information used for occurrence configuration. If structureContextObject  object is given in input the product and configuration context are optional.
